d these constraints to be comparable to those for\nGalactic BNS progenitors. The derived constraints are very strongly influenced\nby the requirement of keeping the binary bound after the second SN and having\nthe merger occur relatively close to the center of the galaxy. These\nconstraints are insensitive to the galaxy's star formation history, provided\nthe stellar populations are older than 1 Gyr.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Oct 2017 16:57:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 1 Dec 2017 18:22:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-04"}
