x 0.3$c, and the \"red\" component has\n$M_\\mathrm{ej}^\\mathrm{red}\\approx 0.04$ M$_\\odot$ and\n$v_\\mathrm{ej}^\\mathrm{red}\\approx 0.1$c. These ejecta masses are broadly\nconsistent with the estimated $r$-process production rate required to explain\nthe Milky Way $r$-process abundances, providing the first evidence that BNS\nmergers can be a dominant site of $r$-process enrichment.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Oct 2017 16:57:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-17"}
