the ejecta with a\nmedium Ye of ~ 0.25. We suggest that a dominant component powering the emission\nis post-merger ejecta, which exhibits that mass ejection after the first\ndynamical ejection is quite efficient. Our results indicate that NS mergers\nsynthesize a wide range of r-process elements and strengthen the hypothesis\nthat NS mergers are the origin of r-process elements in the Universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Oct 2017 16:57:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-17"}
